Class MissingCostEstimationException

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable
      • java.lang.Exception
        • Exceptions.MissingCostEstimationException
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class MissingCostEstimationException
extends java.lang.Exception
    This exception is thrown when a needed object of ICostEstimation is null because no estimation was created for the related requirement analysis.

    When the model has to execute a function on the cost estimation of the opened requirement analysis then it has to be ensured that the cost estimation has been created before and is not null. Otherwise this exception will be thrown.
